  "body": "I am trying to setup Kubernetes v1.0.3 using the hyperkube images. I noticed that for kube-controller-manager, the livenessProbe tries to GET `http://192.168.10.24:10251/healthz`, but the controller-manager actually listens on localhost:\n\n```\n$ sudo netstat -nptul | grep 10252\ntcp        0      0 127.0.0.1:10252         0.0.0.0:*               LISTEN      15568/hyperkube\n```\n\nThus I need to modify the livenessProbe to connect to localhost instead. How do I do that?\n",
